			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Hi
<br />

<br />
 I would like to make a suggestion on a way to fix the mage class with nothing more simple than to adjust the taunt button we have for mage pets. It would work like this:
<br />

<br />
Taunt on:
<br />

<br />
Mage pets increase a Lot in HP and AC and Mitigation but their DPS hits are low. What they are now basically around 85 damage (don't nerf them). This is usefull for a soloig mage or in a situation where mages need to solo and have pet getting aggro. You could turn taunt on when you want a pet to take over tanking from a dead warrior or in emergency situations or simply when you want pet to keep aggro so you could nuke the mob when soloing. The aggro modifer would have to be increased to the same level or more as deafening decoy so that the pet will actually out aggro a tank even sometimes. This can be usefull in groups too when you want the pet to take some hits so the tank doesnt die so quick.
<br />

<br />
This fixes:
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Mage Defense</span> - Due to high aggro, mobs wont summon and kill you straight away. You can also rely more on pet to protect you as a defense measure.
<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Solo effectivness</span> - Due to high aggro and high HP, Mitigation and ac
<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Group usefullness</span> - When the tank dies you can turn aggro on and make pet tank for a while without getting slaughtered straight away.
<br />

<br />
Taunt off:
<br />

<br />
Pets HP decrease as it wont be getting hit anyway (how often do you see your pet getting hit in a group with a tank? Never). Though pets DPS , IE hits go up to around 250/150 damage per hit. This means you are using a pet as dps only and not as a meatshield for defensive purposes. This would keep raid people happy because they would have a pet that does a lot more damage keeping it balanced. It would also not be taunting so it wont be stealing aggro from MA/MT. 
<br />

<br />
This fixes:
<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Raid desireability</span> - pet more usefull at raids as a dps source.
<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Group desireability</span> - Pets doing dps rather than just standing there not getting hit and doing hardly any damage. More dps done in groups.
<br />

<br />

<br />
Now slate this as much as you want. Though to be honest if you look at this you will see it is quite reasonable and it answers a lot of questions to our problems you see people complain about. Before you complain at yet another silly idea take a look again over the situation and ask yourself . Will this benefit me as a mage? Will this make me more wanted? Will this make me be a true master of pets? Will this increase my powers through my pet as a Mage should be?
<br />

<br />
I think you will find it is a yes..
<br />

<br />
Though come ahead with your critics and tell me what you think?</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
