However...
<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">Oh and regarding the Chuzo quote about pets not taking aggro from pc;s. Yes we all know that mate but that would be fixed too. When pet is set to taunt then it taunts like a pc. If it is switched off the pet is regarded the same way it is now with taunt switched off. That gives us the power to control wiether the pet is to be used for DPS or Defenseive </td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />
I don't think we will ever see this concept happen.  For one, a long time ago pets used to be able to tank while PC's were in range.  However, this was a specific change made to prevent pets from ever becoming the intended tanks as there is less risk involved with a disposeable pet tanking vs. a PC.
<br />

<br />
I remember a long time ago in a land far far away (when Kunark was new, heh heh) that one of my favorite groups to exp in was this amazing dungeon called Chardok was me (rogue at the time) a monk, necro, mage, shaman, and cleric.  Sounds kinda odd eh?  Not really, as at the time, as long as you had at least 2 pets involved on the mob's hate list, the pets could act as tanks over the PC's.  The monk would pull, pets would be sent in to attack, shaman would slow, cleric heal, I would backstab.. that's right, backstab the mobs.  Because of their greater aggro generation, I could BS away and not even have to worry about evading, and never once took hits so long as I allowed the pets to attack first.  We would chain pull for hours, and the xp just flew (Chardok and Seb back then were the height of exp, lol)
<br />

<br />
However, I can't remember the exact date or expansion, but a short time later new coding was put into the game to make it what we have today, whereas when ANY PC on the mobs hate list steps into range, it will attack the PC over the pets.  I can't imagine them changing something they purposefully changed many years ago.  Also, I can't imagine, even with OoW, that mage pets will ever be tough enough to tank any kind of raid mobs at that level, let alone exp mobs past the first few tiers of PoP better than a true PC tank.  Just my 2cp.
<br />

<br />
Elder Longfanz Feral Lord</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
